('9c7cf0e4-50ec-4645-a5f4-4a85c8c2c325', '9c6c7ddc-0596-41e5-83b3-b509e8f30b9f', 2, 'Proposed Increase in Directors’ Remuneration/ Meeting Fee', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The agenda paper/memorandum received from the Human Resource Management Division regarding the subject noted above is placed before the Board of Directors for consideration and necessary approval.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Board of Directors in its 59<sup>th</sup> meeting held on July 22, 2022 has approved Rs.50,000/- as Directors&rsquo; Remuneration/ Meeting Fee for Chairman and all Directors, for attending Board and its Committees&rsquo; meetings.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">According to Regulation G-14(1) of the Corporate Governance Regulatory Framework of State Bank of Pakistan, the banks shall pay a reasonable and appropriate remuneration to their board members. The Regulation G-14(2)(v) capped the board remuneration at a maximum limit of 500,000/- for those banks the assets of which are below Rs. 500 billion or those who have below Rs.1 billion after tax profit as per their last audited annual accounts (the Bank of AJK falls in this category).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Considering the subsequent year-on-year increase in inflation and the significant financial growth of the Bank over the years, the current fee doesn&rsquo;t commensurate with the valuable time and efforts contributed by the Board members in improving the overall governance system of the Bank. The fee is also very low w</span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">hen compared to the other public sector banks, as per the available data given as under:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<table class=\"MsoNormalTable\" style=\"margin-left: 23.4pt; border-collapse: collapse; border: none; width: 91.3485%; height: 173.333px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 49.3333px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 18.5285%; border: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 49.3333px; line-height: 1;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"64\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: 13.0pt; mso-line-height-rule: exactly; mso-pagination: none; mso-layout-grid-align: none; vertical-align: baseline;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun; mso-bidi-fo