nt-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Compliance of the Minutes of 75<sup>th</sup> Meeting of the Board of Directors </span></u></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 264.667px;\" rowspan=\"2\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Noted</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 202.667px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 202.667px;\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l4 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">c)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></strong><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Update on Hiring of Consultancy Services for Raising Regulatory Capital Requirements of Scheduled Bank for BAJK</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">It was informed that in response to the letter of Law Department Govt. of AJK, a reply was sent through Finance Department dated February 14, 2024, and the Memorandum of Association of the successful bidder&rsquo;s company was also annexed to the letter. The Bank is uninformed regarding the current status of the matter.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 277.333px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 277.333px;\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l4 level1 lfo3; background: white;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">d)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Establishment of BAJK Exchange Company</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Board was informed that as required by SBP, all the requisite documents have been sent to the State Bank of Pakistan and a positive response is anticipated to be received from the State Bank of Pakistan.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Initiated by the Secretary Finance, Director </span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Mr. Islam Zaib, the Chairman concurred that a meeting of representative(s) of the Board shall be arranged with the Governor State Bank of Pakistan to pursue and expedite the issuance of NOC for BAJK Exchange Company and deliberate on other financial matters. </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 277.333px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">As per telephonic conversation, SBP has scrutinized the documents of BAJK Exchange Company and Fit &amp; Proper Test is under process.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">It is proposed that the requisite process should be undertaken prior to arranging a meeting with the Governor SBP.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 349.323px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 225.729px; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-left: 1pt solid windowtext; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 349.323px;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"69\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; tab-stops: 33.8pt;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">04</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 349.323px;\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Proposed Amendment in <a name=\"_Hlk171801694\"></a>HR Policies &amp; Procedures Manual</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 6.0pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Resolved that </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo4; margin: 6.0pt 0in 6.0pt .25in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">The proposed amendments in Human Resource Policies and Procedures Manual, as recommended by the Board Human Resource Committee, are hereby approved, except the amendment envisaged in Clause 7.5 pertaining to Annual Salary Increase, which shall be revisited by the Board Human Resource Committee.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo4; margin: 6.0pt 0in 6.0pt .25in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">The Basic Pay of the employees shall be revisited by the Board Human Resource Committee in comparison to other banks. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo4; margin: 6.0pt 0in 6.0pt .25in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">c)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Atleast one Board meeting shall be arranged in each region of the Bank&rsquo;s operations, namely, Rawalakot, Kotli and Mirpur.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 349.323px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: center; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo8;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: center; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo8;\" align=\"center\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Amendments approved by the Board have been incorporated in the HR Policies &amp; Procedures Manual. For amendment in Clause 7.5, please refer Agenda No. 04.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: center; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo8;\" align=\"center\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 110%; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 110%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Please refer Agenda No. 04.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: center; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo8;\" align=\"center\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 110%; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">c)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 110%; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Noted</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 160px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 225.729px; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-left: 1pt solid windowtext; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 160px;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"69\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; tab-stops: 33.8pt;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">05</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 160px;\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Proposed Increase in Directors&rsquo; Remuneration/ Meeting Fee</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Resolved that increase in the Directors&rsquo; Remuneration/ Meeting Fee from Rs.50,000/- to Rs.100,000/- per meeting for Chairman and all Directors, for attending Board and its Committees&rsquo; meetings, as recommended by the Board Human Resource Committee, is hereby approved with effect from July 01, 2024.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 160px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Decision implemented <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">with effect from July 01, 2024.</span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 346.396px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 225.729px; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-left: 1pt solid windowtext; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 346.396px;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"69\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; tab-stops: 33.8pt;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">06</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 346.396px;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Hiring of Management Internees</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 6.0pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Resolved that </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l6 level1 lfo5; margin: 5.0pt 0in 5.0pt .25in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Hiring of 50 Management Internees (15 each for <a name=\"_Hlk171801916\"></a>Rawalakot, Kotli, and Mirpur Regions and 05 for Muzaffarabad Region) are hereby approved with relaxation in age limit from 27 to 35 years. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l6 level1 lfo5; margin: 5.0pt 0in 5.0pt .25in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Curtailing minimum educational passing marks criteria from 70% to 60% should be discussed and decided by the Board Human Resource Committee and should be presented for endorsement of the Board in its next meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l6 level1 lfo5; margin: 5.0pt 0in 5.0pt .25in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">The minimum salary of the Internees shall be discussed by the Board Human Resource Committee to bring it at par with atleast the minimum wage announced by the Government.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 346.396px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Please refer Agenda No. 05.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 133.333px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 225.729px; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-left: 1pt solid windowtext; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 133.333px;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"69\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; tab-stops: 33.8pt;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">08</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 133.333px;\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Minutes of the Board Subcommittees</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top: 6.0pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Resolved that the minutes of the Board Subcommittees, circulated to the Board as a part of agenda, are hereby ratified/ approved.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 133.333px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The decision was communicated to the Secretaries of the respective Committees.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 234.667px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 225.729px; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-left: 1pt solid windowtext; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 359px;\" rowspan=\"2\" valign=\"top\" width=\"69\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; tab-stops: 33.8pt;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">09.</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 234.667px;\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Other Items </span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; background: white;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Regularization of the Contractual Employees</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">The Board, upon considering the recommendation of the Board Human Resource Committee, has approved the regularization of six contractual employees (as per list provided by the Management). This approval is subject to the employees\' satisfactory performance and other terms and conditions as stated in the Bank\'s Human Resource Policy.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 234.667px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Decision was communicated to the relevant division. </span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 124.333px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 124.333px;\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; background: white;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Increase in Basic Pay @10% to all Employees across the board</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Resolved that increase in basic pay @ 10% (applicable on the salary as withdrawn on December 31, 2023) to all the employees of the Bank across the board, as recommended by the Board Human Resource Committee, is hereby approved with effect from July 01, 2024.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 124.333px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Decision has been implemented.</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 392.667px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 225.729px; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-left: 1pt solid windowtext; border-image: initial; border-top: none; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 392.667px;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"69\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; tab-stops: 33.8pt;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">10</span></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 465.625px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 392.667px;\" valign=\"top\" width=\"340\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><strong><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext;\">Other Items- Career Path for the Workforce, Working through Third-Party Service Provider</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Resolved that the matter be referred to the Bank Human Resource Committee to look into the possibility of defining career path for the workforce performing duties through Third Party Service Provider after following the rules and procedures as laid down in the Human Resource Policies and Procedures Manual.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes;\">&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 357.125px; border-top: none; border-left: none; border-bottom: 1pt solid windowtext; border-right: 1pt solid windowtext; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 392.667px;\" width=\"214\">\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The agenda was presented in 10<sup>th</sup> BHRC meeting held on August 02, 2024 and after detailed deliberation, the Committee resolved as under:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Quote \"Since the Recruitment Policy of the Bank is neither applied on the employees of the third-party service provider, nor any policy can be made for career planning and induction/ regularization of these resources. However, they may continue provision of services to the Bank until required by the Bank. Moreover, as and when any vacancy arises in the Bank, and the Bank start hiring process as per Recruitment Policy of the Bank, these resources can apply for induction in the Bank, and Bank, keeping in view their services and past performance may give them due weightage at the time of interview\". Unquote</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: 4.5pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -13.5pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span class=\"fontstyle01\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong></span><!--[endif]--><span class=\"fontstyle01\"><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun;\">Proposal</span></u></strong></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: 4.5pt; text-align: justify;\"><span class=\"fontstyle01\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun;\">The Board is requested to review the compliance report and pass the following resolution:</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: justify; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">&ldquo;Resolved that the </span><span class=\"fontstyle01\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: SimSun;\">compliance report of the Management on various decisions taken by the Board of Directors up to its </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black;\">77<sup>th</sup> meeting held on July 15, 2024 </span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">(including Compliance Report of 76<sup>th</sup> Board Meeting held on July 12, 2024</span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black;\">), is hereby recorded.&rdquo;</span></p>', 2, NULL, '2024-08-06 05:55:03', '2024-08-08 13:36:39'),
('9cb59188-61a3-4f0b-97dc-4d09c470e379', '9cb2f0b9-53c0-4151-9eb7-a505ce2d2b1f', 2, 'Brief on the status of the Appeal filed in Supreme Court of AJK  regarding Procurement of Core Banking Software', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; color: black; mso-color-alt: windowtext; background: white;\">It may be recalled that</span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"> on the basis of writ petitions filed before the honorable High Court of AJK regarding Core Banking Software dated December 07, 2023; the judgment of the High Court was issued on July 03, 2024, delineated below:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">&ldquo;In our considered opinion, impugned proceedings are not sustainable in the eyes of law requiring a fresh look into the matter by the relevant quarters. For the above multiple reasons, the supra titled writ petitions are accepted. All the proceedings impugned herein are overturned. The relevant quarters are directed to place the matter in special meeting of the cabinet immediately in view of Rule 29(1) of the AJK Rules of Business 1985, simultaneously informing the Public Accounts Committee as well. Needful is required to be done in this regard within one month and its compliance report shall be submitted before the Registrar of this court.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">It may further be recalled that the Board of Directors, during its 76<sup>th</sup> and 77<sup>th</sup> meetings held on July 12, 2024 and July 15, 2024 respectively, thoroughly deliberated the High Court Orders and the required course of action to be undertaken in this regard. The Board therein has resolved that an appeal shall be filed with the Supreme Court of AJK for suspension of the AJK High Court&rsquo;s Orders.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">In compliance of the Board decision, leave to appeal against the decision was filed in honorable Supreme Court of AJK on July 25, 2024. In its first hearing dated July 30, 2024, the honorable Supreme Court suspended the impugned judgment of High Court till further orders:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">&ldquo;The learned counsel for the parties argued the case at great length. After hearing them, we are of the view that this case satisfies the ingredients governing the interim injunction i.e., prime facie arguable case, balance of convenience and irreparable loss, hence, we deem it appropriate to suspend the impugned judgment of the High Court dated 03.07.2024 till further orders. However, the concerned authorities are restrained from taking any action in furtherance of impugned proceeding. These applications shall be taken up along with the petitions for leave to appeal on completion. The matter shall now be taken up by the full Court.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Order of the Supreme Court is attached as Annex-A. Moreover, next date of hearing in Supreme Court is August 23, 2024. </span></p>', 3, NULL, '2024-08-07 13:14:06', '2024-08-07 13:14:06');
INSERT INTO `agenda_items` (`id`, `meeting_id`, `user_id`, `title`, `description`, `order`, `deleted_at`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
('9cb7be4c-5c5e-43b1-9bee-61e986b882e2', '9cb2f0b9-53c0-4151-9eb7-a505ce2d2b1f', 2, 'Proposed Amendments in Human Resource Policies and Procedures Manual', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The agenda paper/memorandum received from the Human Resource Management Division regarding the subject noted above is placed before the Board of Directors for consideration and necessary approval.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">It may be recalled that certain Amedements in Human Resource Policies &amp; Procedures Manual were presented to the Board in its 76<sup>th</sup> meeting held on July 12, 2024 for consideration and approval. The Board during the meeting resolved that:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The proposed amendments in Human Resource Policies and Procedures Manual, as recommended by the Board Human Resource Committee, are&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; hereby approved, except the amendment envisaged in Clause 7.5 pertaining to Annual Salary Increase, which shall be revisited by the Board&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Human&nbsp; Resource Committee.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: normal; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo1; margin: 6.0pt 0in 0in .5in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The Basic Pay of the employees shall be revisited by the Board Human Resource Committee in comparison to other banks.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The agenda regarding above was presented in 10<sup>th</sup> meeting of BHRC held on August 02, 2024 and after deliberation, the Committee resolved as under:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo2; margin: 0in 0in 6.0pt .5in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The Committee recommended the proposed revision in Annual Increase structure to the Board for approval (attached to Annex-A).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The Committee further recommended the proposed revised basic pay scales from Messenger to OG-I to the Board of Directors for their consideration and approval (attached to Annex-A) and advised the Management that a comprehensive exercise should be carried out in comparison with other peer Banks and resubmit the revision in pay scales from AVP and above grade executives for perusal of the Committee.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The BHRC after thorough deliberation recommended the above agenda for approval of the Board.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">5.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Proposal</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Board is requested to review the proposed amendments in Human Resource Policies and Procedures Manual and pass the following resolution:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">&ldquo;Resolved that the proposed amendments in Human Resource Policies and Procedures Manual, as recommended by the Board Human Resource Committee, are hereby approved.&rdquo;</span></p>', 4, NULL, '2024-08-08 15:10:56', '2024-08-08 15:11:10'),
('9cb7c076-3f18-4924-8911-f6f541760f1b', '9cb2f0b9-53c0-4151-9eb7-a505ce2d2b1f', 2, 'Hiring of Management Internees (Batch-2)', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The agenda paper/memorandum received from the Human Resource Management Division regarding the subject noted above is placed before the Board of Directors for consideration and necessary approval.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">It may be recalled that regarding hiring of Management Internees (Batch-2) the Board during its 76<sup>th</sup> meeting held on July 12, 2024 has resolved that:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&nbsp; a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Hiring of 50 Management Internees (15 each for Rawalakot, Kotli, and Mirpur Regions and 05 for Muzaffarabad Region) are hereby approved with&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;relaxation in age limit from 27 to 35 years. </span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraph\" style=\"margin-top: 6pt; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; padding-left: 40px;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&nbsp;b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">Curtailing minimum educational passing marks criteria from 70% to 60% should be discussed and decided by the Board Human Resource&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Committee and should be presented for endorsement of the Board in its next meeting.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3; margin: 6.0pt 0in .0001pt .5in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">c)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">The minimum salary of the Internees shall be discussed by the Board Human Resource Committee to bring it at par with atleast the minimum wage announced by the Government.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The agenda regarding above was presented in 10<sup>th</sup> meeting of BHRC held on August 02, 2024 and the point-wise responses submitted to the Committee are as under:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo4;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp; &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">It is submitted that the criteria for hiring of Management Internees has been defined by the Management internally and there is no policy violation. Minimum educational passing marks criteria was fixed as 70% for applying for the positions of Management Internees. However, it has been observed during the hiring process that a large number of candidate could not be shortlisted due to less than 70% marks in their last educational degree, due to which the required number of Management Internees could not be hired, particularly for Mirpur and Kotli Region Branches. In our opinion 70% qualifying criteria is on the higher side. If criteria is announced on 70% marks, we could not be able, even to select our required minimum number of Management Interns and that at 70% minimum educational passing marks very limited number of candidates will qualify to apply for the positions.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">Therefore, it is proposed that the candidates having 60% and above marks in their last educational degree be allowed for applying for the positions of Management Internees to meet the demand of Management Internees.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo4;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp; &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">As far minimum wages are concerned it is submitted that at present Management Interns are being paid Rs. 30,000/- as stipend, which is too good as compared to the stipend paid by other Banks. As per market search recently UBL has offered the positions of Management Internees @ Rs. 20,000/- per month and Meezan Bank is paying Rs. 15,000/- per month, whereas BAJK has already paid a reasonable stipend to their Management Internees.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">Considering the comparatively lesser financial impact and encouraging feedback for Management Interns, BHRC was requested to accord approval for hiring the services of Management Interns with relaxation in minimum educational passing marks criteria from 70% to 60% so that the issue of staff shortage can be resolved to a certain extent.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">5.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold; mso-no-proof: yes;\">The Committee after considering the request of Management, recommended hiring of 50 Management Interns (15 each for Mirpur, Rawalakot, Kotli and 05 for Islamic Banking Division) @ Rs. 30,000/- per month (with relaxation in age &amp; qualifying marks criteria) to the Board of Directors for approval.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">6.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Proposal</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Board is requested to pass the following resolution:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">&ldquo;Resolved that hiring of 50 Management Internees (15 each for Rawalakot, Kotli, and Mirpur Regions and 05 for Islamic Banking Division) are hereby approved with relaxation in age limit from 27 to 35 years and curtailing minimum educational passing marks criteria from 70% to 60%.&rdquo;</span></p>', 5, NULL, '2024-08-08 15:16:59', '2024-08-08 15:16:59'),
('9cb7c1fc-2cee-40b5-81a2-affcd4cd06f0', '9cb2f0b9-53c0-4151-9eb7-a505ce2d2b1f', 2, 'Engagement of Testing Firm for Induction of Fresh Staff', '<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">1.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The agenda paper/memorandum received from the Human Resource Management Division regarding the subject noted above is placed before the Board of Directors for consideration and necessary approval.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">2.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">As per Recruitment Policy of the Bank, induction of MTOs/ GBOs/ BDOs/ Cos/ Tellers shall be carried out through a competitive examination, conducted through a testing agency (IBP, NTS etc.).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">3.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp; </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">In compliance of the above-mentioned Clause and to start the hiring process for the aforementioned positions, advertisements were placed in the Newspapers on 15-07-2022, 05-08-2022, 07-10-2022, 16-11-2022, 04-05-2023, 08-11-2023, 01-02-2024 and 05-06- 2024. The task could not be completed for various reasons, like non participation of the companies, not being able to qualify on the required criteria etc. and most recently, companies have brought the complaints against each other on account of ongoing investigations in FIA and other agencies.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">4.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\"> &nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">In current circumstances when Bank is not in a position of hiring a testing company, the turnover rate is extremely high and due to employee\'s switchover, branches are in jeopardy. Bank is currently facing acute shortage of staff and in recent past, when the Bank hired 57 candidates in different categories, only 12 out of 57 selected candidates joined the Bank. Moreover, an advertisement was published for hiring of 45 Cash Sorters and 35 GBOs which is still pending as testing company has not been hired so far.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo2;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">5.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Accordingly, the matter was placed before the Board HR Committee which, after detailed deliberation resolved that the testing requirement is one of the mandatory pre-requisites for induction of MTOs/ GBOs/ BDOs/ Tellers, and allowing relaxation of the condition does not fall within the purview of this Committee, therefore, the request may be presented to the Board for appropriate decision by giving three options of conducting test directly either through NTS, IBP (as per policy) or by the Bank.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo1;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">6.<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><strong style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;\"><u><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">Proposal</span></u></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .25in; text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Board is requested that keeping in view the problem faced by the Bank in hiring of testing firm and immediate operational requirement of the Bank, one of the following options may be cosidered and accordingly Bank may be allowed to proceed further accordingly for recruitment of assistants/tellers and General Banking officers:</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">a)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Bank will conduct test through direct arrangements with NTS (Govt. owned Institution).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">b)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Bank will conduct test through BIF (NIBAF Pakistan) (A subsidiary of SBP).</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNoSpacing\" style=\"margin-left: .5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -.25in; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo3;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">c)<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Calibri;\">The Bank will conduct test at its own arrangements.</span></p>', 6, NULL, '2024-08-08 15:21:14', '2024-08-08 15:51:19'),
